snippet.title: How Robert Pattinson Pulled Off A Hollywood Miracle
snippet.description:
For a big part of his career, it seemed Robert Pattinson would forever be associated with the Twilight Saga.  Though, he wasn't the biggest fan of Twilight in general, so Robbert Pattinson set out to change audience perspective.  Working on some critically acclaimed indie projects, Robert Pattinson escaped Twilight by showing off his range as an actor, and choosing the right projects at the right time.  But what movie specifically separated him from the sparkling vampires of Twilight? 

#robertpattinson #twilight #nerdstalgic

snippet.title: 007 James Bond Spectre movie reaction first time watching
snippet.description:
007 James Bond returns in Spectre and this is an interesting one following up Skyfall.

Badd Medicine here and it Spectre movie reaction time! Daniel Craig again does a fantastic job (in our opinion) and the addition of Christoph Waltz, Léa Seydoux, and big Dave Bautista (former WWE superstar) were great! It was nice to see this story pull from Casino Royale, Quantum of Solace, and Skyfall. The big reveal of James Bond and Blofeld growing up together of sorts. Blofeld take down of the double 0's was an interesting take with the technology and Blofeld claiming to be the one behind all of Bond's darker days. And Bond ends up with Mr. White's daughter?! That was an interesting twist. Not as much action in this one compared to Quantum of Solace and Skyfall.

Next up, No time to Die movie reaction! Can't wait!

snippet.title: Simply FANTASTIC! Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings movie reaction first time watching
snippet.description:
MCU reaction is here! Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings is an awesome surprise and we say that because we knew nothing about this story and it was absolutely great we didn't! 

Badd Medicine here and we have a Marvel reaction ready for you! Our first time watching Shang-Chi and it was HIGHLY entertaining and would recommend everyone to watch Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings full movie if you can. A lot of marvel Iron man references in this one! And we also get introduced to a lot of wild animals here. Those lion like creatures and who can forget Morris!? That animal will be a high seller in the merch department for sure! We also get the Mandarin from Iron man 3! The characters of Shang-Chi and Katie will be a fantastic addition to the MCU! Wong from Dr. Strange was fighting Abomination!?! And seems to be training him?! Will we see him Spider Man No way home? Or future MCU movies? And those end credit scenes with Captain Marvel and Bruce Banner will be great to see how this all gets tied in. Andrew thinks we may get Adam Warlock? What's your thoughts?

What was your Shang Chi reaction? What was your favorite part of the movie? And what do you think the Shang Chi post credit scenes will lead to?

snippet.title: WOW!!!!!! James Bond No Time to Die movie reaction first time watching
snippet.description:
007 James Bond No time to die reaction is here and wow what a movie this was!

Badd Medicine here and it No time to die movie reaction time! Folks, this was a heck of a movie. I know some will disagree with that and that is ok. All a matter of perspective. Daniel Craig's epic portrayal of the iconic is James Bond is one of the best. The soundtrack (the score) by Hans Zimmer is widely fantastic! The callbacks in this movie were great! We see Spectre is still a large part of this movie as Blofeld tries early to make Bond believe that Madeleine (Léa Seydoux) is with Spectre. We see Bond leave and get pulled in by Fleix (Jeffrey Wright) to go get Dr. Valdo Obruchev as these crazy nanobots can wipe you out based on DNA programing. Just wild! Bond teams up with Paloma (Ana de Armas) to go and get Obruchev. They get him and new guy Logan Ash was working with our main villain Lyutsifer Safin (Rami Malek) and of course Safin was the man who took our Mr. White wife and we see that right away in the beginning with the quick flash back for Madeleine. Fast forward to the end, the guts it took to take out Bond at the end was an interesting choice. We didn't mind it and yeah, they could've made an attempt to save Bond and try to test him, but if they wouldn't be able to figure it out, bad things might have happened and James Bond wouldn't want to go through life like that. Right? It was an emotional James Bond death scene. I understand why some would be upset, but he did say in the beginning "double 0's have a short life expectancy" tough, emotional scene. If you didn't like, let us know. Big shout out to all the men and women who worked on the Daniel Craig Bonds over the years to delivery quality entertainment! And Cheers to Daniel Craig on a fantastic run!

What was your No time to die reaction? Did they make the right move at the end for Bond? Who should be the next James Bond?

snippet.title: What. Just. Happened!? The Matrix (1999) movie reaction first time watching
snippet.description:
Keanu Reeves was awesome in one of the most epic films of all time, The Matrix! And this is Diamond Dave's first time watching. 

Badd Medicine here and it is The Matrix movie reaction time! The Matrix was a trend setting movie back in 1999. Can't tell how many times we have heard, "Do you want the Red pill or the Blue Pill?" Laurence Fishburne as Morpheus crushed the role. Carrie-Anne Moss as Trinity also knocked it out of the park and of course Keanu Reeves as Neo did fantastic. The kung fu Neo vs Morpheus was fantastic. Those 2 must have had fun filming that sequence. Also would like to highlight the The Matrix lobby scene was insane with their graphics too. Felt some John Wick in here and Bill and Ted. Great to get those vibes. As you know by now The Matrix Resurrections is going to be out real quick here. 

What was your reaction to The Matrix? You looking forward to The Matrix Resurrections movie?

snippet.title: Train to Busan movie reaction first time watching
snippet.description:
Train to Busan was surprising really good. And it was refreshing to have something slightly different about the zombies.

Badd Medicine here and it Train to Busan reaction time! Really well done for a zombie movie. All the characters were great and Gong Yoo as Seok-woo, Diamond Dave just kept thinking of Squid game. The MVP character of this movie was Ma Dong-seok as Sang-hwa. Great job by Su-an Kim as Soo-an, she did great as the daughter. The zombies brought something different for us. We are hardcore fans of The Walking Dead as you may know, the zombies have been around for awhile, so they are moving a little slower. Seeing these zombies and the rage they have was intense. And something new for us, once it was dark, the zombies couldn't see! It was great! Our only nitpick was the way the Seok-Woo went out. He didn't need to have his hand there. Only disappointing part. We highly recommend watching full movie if you haven't seen it yet.

What was your reaction to Train to Busan? Was did you think of the zombies not being able to see in the dark?

Shout out to the editor of this video George Bina: https://youtube.com/c/Georgebinaa

snippet.title: Baahubali The Beginning movie reaction first time watching | Prabhas | Tamannaah Bhatia
snippet.description:
Baahubali the Beginning movie reaction has arrived!

Badd Medicine here and it Baahubali reaction time! Full group reaction here folks! Baahubali did not disappoint and dare we say maybe even better than KGF?! Tamannaah Bhatia as Avanthika did a fantastic job. They could've given her a few more actions scenes with her fight style. Prabhas as Shivudu, Amarendra Baahubali, Mahendra Baahubali did great! Multiple character role and he had a ton of charisma. The character had a ton of power and could take on the world except for one man, the traitor, Sathyaraj as Kattappa! What a twist that was at the end. And the Baahubali end scene was an epic piece of action! The invitation of the action was some we haven't seen! Over all we would highly recommend for people to watch Baahubali the beginning full movie when they can.

snippet.title: WHAT A TWIST!!! First time watching Parasite movie reaction
snippet.description:
Badd Medicine here and its Parasite reaction time

Folks, WOW! that last 30 mins was absolutely wild! We can see why Parasite won the awards it did. We honestly thought this was going to be a comedy, shame on us. This twist was amazing. Well done by everyone involved. 

Jobless, penniless, and, above all, hopeless, the unmotivated patriarch, Ki-taek, and his equally unambitious family--his supportive wife, Chung-sook; his cynical twentysomething daughter, Ki-jung, and his college-age son, Ki-woo--occupy themselves by working for peanuts in their squalid basement-level apartment. Then, by sheer luck, a lucrative business proposition will pave the way for an ingeniously insidious scheme, as Ki-woo summons up the courage to pose as an English tutor for the teenage daughter of the affluent Park family. Now, the stage seems set for an unceasing winner-take-all class war.

snippet.title: 7 YEARS PER HOUR?! WHAT!?!?!?! First time watching INTERSTELLAR movie reaction
snippet.description:
Badd Medicine here and its Interstellar reaction time

What a wild and emotional ride Interstellar was! Christopher Nolan and his crew nailed this one! Matthew McConaughey and Anne Hathaway crushed it! And what do you know... a heel turn by Matt Damon!!! Did not see that coming at all. And lets talk about the 7 years per hour... holy cow! That scene from Matthew McConaughey was so dang good! Did not expect to get the emotional and getting the introduction of Casey Affleck and Jessica Chastian was wild to see after 23 years of only what seemed to be an hour of time. And also cant forget the score of this film by Hans Zimmer. Amazing! Can Hans Zimmer just do every film? That would be great. This movie was great and we didn't expect it to be this good. Bravo to the crew and cast!

In Earth's future, a global crop blight and second Dust Bowl are slowly rendering the planet uninhabitable. Professor Brand (Michael Caine), a brilliant NASA physicist, is working on plans to save mankind by transporting Earth's population to a new home via a wormhole. But first, Brand must send former NASA pilot Cooper (Matthew McConaughey) and a team of researchers through the wormhole and across the galaxy to find out which of three planets could be mankind's new home.

snippet.title: Time to Dream within a Dream! First time watching INCEPTION movie reaction
snippet.description:
Badd Medicine here and its Inception reaction time

Thank you @nicholasdyee for your cover of Hans Zimmer's "Time" for more check out his awesome channel https://www.youtube.com/@UCYmtA5JyueBoUuLdS90fvvQ 

Inception is a mind-bending thriller that takes the audience on a thrilling journey through the depths of the subconscious. Directed by Christopher Nolan, the film is a masterful exploration of the power of the human mind and the lengths people will go to achieve their goals.

The plot centers on a team of skilled thieves who enter people's dreams to steal their secrets. The stakes are high as they take on their most challenging job yet, an impossible task that involves planting an idea in someone's mind. As they navigate the surreal landscapes of the dream world, the lines between reality and illusion blur, creating an unpredictable and riveting experience.

The cast is outstanding, with Leonardo DiCaprio leading the pack with a standout performance as the conflicted protagonist, Dom Cobb. His emotional journey is at the heart of the story, and he delivers a compelling and nuanced portrayal of a man haunted by his past. The ensemble cast includes Ken Watanabe, Joseph Gordon-Levitt, Marion Cotillard, Elliot Page, Tom Hardy, Dileep Rao, Cillian Murphy, Tom Berenger, and Michael Caine.

The film's special effects are breathtaking, with stunning visual effects that transport the audience into a world of shifting perspectives and impossible physics. The dreamscapes are beautifully rendered, creating an otherworldly atmosphere that is both disorienting and captivating.

snippet.title: HILAROUSLY Good! First time watching The Nice Guys movie reaction
snippet.description:
Join this channel to get access to perks:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCqAkK44QDpqueoEIKO1AymA/join

Badd Medicine here and its The Nice Guys reaction time

The Nice Guys is a 2016 American neo-noir buddy action comedy film directed and co-written (alongside Anthony Bagarozzi) by Shane Black, produced by Joel Silver, and starring Russell Crowe and Ryan Gosling in the title roles with Angourie Rice, Matt Bomer, Margaret Qualley, Keith David and Kim Basinger in supporting roles. Set in 1977 Los Angeles, the film focuses on private eye Holland March (Gosling) and tough enforcer for hire Jackson Healy (Crowe) who team up to investigate the disappearance of a teenage girl (Qualley).

Set in 1977 Los Angeles, "The Nice Guys" follows private eye Holland March, who's hired to investigate the supposed survival of a deceased porn star, Misty Mountain. His investigation entangles him with Amelia Kuttner, a woman linked to Misty's endeavors. Violent enforcer Jackson Healy is hired to deter March, but they join forces to find Amelia and unravel the mystery surrounding her. They discover Amelia's involvement in a controversial "experimental film" exposing the collusion between car makers and the suppression of catalytic converters. As they chase leads, including the film's missing footage, they become targets for a ruthless hit man named John Boy.

Amidst a series of murders and political intrigue, March and Healy navigate a web of deception that implicates high-ranking officials. Amelia's film, eventually projected at the Los Angeles Auto Show, reveals the auto executives' guilt. As the truth emerges, Healy and March expose the crimes but struggle against powerful forces. The story culminates in a rooftop showdown and the film's screening.

While March, Healy, and March's daughter Holly survive, Amelia is tragically killed. The film ends with March and Healy starting their own detective agency, "The Nice Guys," showing their resilience in a corrupt world.

snippet.title: Living & Dying Alone In Singapore: Facing Lonely Deaths | Dead Alone In Singapore - Part 1
snippet.description:
In recent years, more lonely deaths were reported in the media and at least 37 cases were reported in 2023. Who were they and how did they landed up dying alone? 
 
In part one of this series, we meet an expert, Corinne Ghoh who decided to track the cases as there were no official data, uncovering the social dimension of this phenomenon. We also meet Rahman Razali, the trauma cleaner being tasked with cleaning the remnants of decomposed bodies, reveals stories of solitary lives. 

Heng Aik Min, who is fear of dying alone at home, shares his worries and how he is trying to prevent his body from decomposing till the state that would affect others. And Linda Tan, an eldercare programme executive, who claims unclaimed body and execute their last rites.

WATCH MORE Dead Alone In Singapore
Part 2: https://youtu.be/Q1gVNrnkmEE
Part 3: https://youtu.be/jP9HA8syZl0

=====
About the show: Lonely death looks to be a growing phenomenon here in Singapore. We speak to those living alone, to those impact by such tragic deaths and those who deal with the aftermath of theses deaths.

snippet.title: What Happens After Someone Dies Alone? | Dead Alone In Singapore - Part 2/3 | Full Episode
snippet.description:
Trauma cleaner Rahman Razali meets a new client – Bobby. Bobby’s distant aunt died alone and was undiscovered for a few days. After her home has been thoroughly disinfected, Bobby searches for clues about how to settle his aunt’s affairs – and makes some surprising discoveries about a woman he hardly knew.

Meanwhile, eldercare programme executive Linda Tan receives an urgent request for assistance with the funeral of a complete stranger. An elderly man with no next-of-kin was found dead in a public toilet. Linda knows nothing about this man. Can she give him a respectful farewell?

As he deals with an increasing number of funerals for the lonely dead, 26-year-old funeral director Jack Lee finds himself grappling with his feelings about dying – and living – alone. What 
will he choose to do to raise awareness about an unfortunate phenomenon?

In Part 2 of this series, afterlife service providers show us what it takes to put the lonely dead to rest – regardless of faith and financial status.

snippet.title: Can We Prevent Lonely Deaths In Singapore? | Dead Alone In Singapore - Part 3/3 | Full Episode
snippet.description:
Trauma cleaner Rahman Razali and fourth-generation funeral director Jack Lee use TikTok to highlight the issue of those who die alone. Their viral videos aim to raise awareness, encourage donations for funeral costs, and promote vigilance and compassion within our communities. 
 
65-year-old Heng Aik Min, serves as a stark reminder of the isolation many elderly individuals face. Living alone with no next of kin, he volunteers his time to send off others who have died alone, exemplifying the loneliness and selflessness that define his twilight years.
 
Eldercare programme executive Linda Tan ensures Mr Ho, who was alone in life, is not alone in death, with the help of her volunteers. Through the work of afterlife service providers and the experiences of lonely individuals, this episode explores how everyone can play a part in preventing undetected deaths.

snippet.title: 7 Of The Most Faked Seafoods In The World | Big Business | Business Insider
snippet.description:
According to the ocean-conservation nonprofit Oceana, seafood may be one of the most commonly fraudulent foods we come in contact with. Your red snapper could actually be a tilapia fillet. That wild-caught salmon? It could be farm-raised. Crab, lobster, and scallops have also been victims of fraudulent swaps — some of the substitutions could harm human health. But there are also entire criminal rings smuggling seafood across the world. They often fish illegally and have been involved in human trafficking. Why is it so hard to catch bad actors in seafood supply chains? And how can we ensure we're getting the seafood on the label?

snippet.title: 知る人ぞ知る！京都の山奥にある唯一無二のパン屋！薪窯で焼かれる素朴で最高のパン！
snippet.description:
自然とともにいきるパン屋さんです。
電気はほとんど使わず、パン生地は手捏ねし自然発酵させる。
そして自家製薪窯でパンを焼き上げます。
パン職人である太田光軌（おおたこうき）さんは「ペイザン・ブーランジェ（農家パン屋）」の生き方を学びにフランスに渡ります。
日本に戻り、山奥の古民家で唯一無二のパン屋をご夫婦で営んでいます。

「FOOD☆STAR」チャンネル登録はこちら
https://tinyurl.com/trwc8cjv

BGM提供：
若林タカツグ

━━━━━━━━

店名：農家パン 弥栄窯（やさかがま）
住所：京都府京丹後市弥栄町須川3084

公式サイト：
https://yasakagama.com/

https://www.instagram.com/yasakagama/

日本に戻り、山奥の古民家で唯一無二のパン屋をご夫婦で営んでいます。

snippet.title: A Woman runs a bakery deep in the mountains | wood fired oven | Sourdough bread making in Japan
snippet.description:
Kisan Seisakusho
Bakery specializing in home-cultivated leaven (sourdough) opened in 2021 in a 140-year-old renovated private house.Azusa Omori starts by kneading the dough for all bread by hand.
She also does not use a fermentation machine, but instead controls the temperature in the room and the placement of the dough to achieve the best fermentation conditions for the bread dough.She then bakes the bread and cookies in her own wood-fired oven. On weekends, Omori's mother helps out at the store as sales staff.
Omori trained at the famous Okinawan bakery Munakata-do, and then at the farm bakery "Chantou La Vie" in Normandy, France. 
She says her first encounter with "Country bread" was when he was a kindergarten student at a school where "Nova" was selling "Country bread"

Name：Kisan Seisakusho
address： 3141-1 Senba-cho, Sano, Tochigi
Instagram :https://www.instagram.com/kisanseisakujo/

Kinds of leaven
1, Sourdough
2, Raisin yeast liquid（No sugar）
3. Rice and Koji leaven

Shoot and Edit：Reiya Watanabe

snippet.title: Bread making by the man known as the "Prodigy" |  Sourdough bread making in Japan
snippet.description:
Akira Enomoto served as the Japanese head chef of the famous French bakery "Dominique SAIBRON", and was also involved in the product development and launch of the bakery and café. He is one of Japan's leading bakers. He opened "Pain des Philosophes" in Kagurazaka, where European culture has taken root,
He decided to make only the bread he want to make. And the bakery offers about 20 kinds of breads made from various natural leavens and 15 kinds of flours.

Baker: Akira Enomoto
Bakery`s name: Pain des Philosophes
Location: 1-8 Higashigokencho Shinjuku ward, Tokyo
https://maps.app.goo.gl/3B7XxCFf2WxyG2Pw5
Instagram：
https://www.instagram.com/pain_des_philosophes/

The type of leaven
・Sourdough
・Raisin leaven
・Green raisin leaven
・Apple leaven
・Koji (麹) leaven
・Sourdough（Pate Fermentee：Made from straight method French bread dough fermented for 3 hours）
・semidry yeast

Additional explanation by Mr. Enomoto
※He use natural leavens made from fruits in liquid form. This allows the individuality of the liquid leaven to be more apparent in the bread. For this reason, he use different natural liquid leavens according to the characteristics of the bread.
※He often uses a mix of liquid leaven from fruit and sourdough (Pate Fermentee). liquid leavens from fruit are also added with sugar during the feeding process, so they remain sweet. If you want to increase the fermentation power of the dough, It might be better to add sourdough (Pate Fermentee) . You can get more fermentation power in dough as keeping the flavor of the bread you want to make.
※"Pain de Lodeve" takes a 12-hour autolyze. This process brings out the true flavor of the flour and increases its Umami.
※Comparing Japan and France, the level of technology and knowledge is higher in Japan, but whether Japanese bread tastes better is another question, he said. France is an agricultural country, and its flour, butter, and other dairy products are of high quality. Japan has compensated for such disadvantages with its technological capabilities, but recently, flour and other Japanese ingredients have become tastier.

Shoot and Edit：Reiya Watanabe

snippet.title: Quiet Space, Wood-fired Oven, and Baking | The Moon and Clown | Sourdough Bread in Japan
snippet.description:
Drawing spring water, chopping wood, and baking bread. A simple life and bread made with care.
The owner of "The Moon and the Clown", Yoshinao Nagaya, quit his job as a civil servant and started baking bread in the storage of his parents' house.
The store and house, built in 2020 by a renowned architect, are in perfect harmony with the bread. Customers come from far and wide to visit.

Owner; Yoshinao Nagaya
Bakery`s name: The Moon and the Clown
Location: 2-93 Hazaka, Nakanotomachi, Kashima-gun, Ishikawa, Japan

Types of bread
1, Levain
2, Rye sour
3, Hops leaven
4, Raisin leaven
5. Yogurt leaven
6. Sourdough made with hops and raisins
7. Industrial yeast

Hops leaven Ingredients
Hops, potatoes, apples, Koji
(It is said that Koji increases the decomposition power of wheat and brings out the sweetness of wheat.)

Raisin leaven Ingredients
Raisins, granulated sugar
(The addition of sugar also leaves a sweetness in the liquid leaven, which is used as a fruity sweetener in combination with the power of fermentation.)

Filming and Editing： REIYA Watanabe

snippet.title: A cheerful man's healing baking in nature | Bäckerei Nagaya | German Sourdough Bread in Japan
snippet.description:
Mike was born in Germany into a family of bakers and worked as a craftsman in an organic bakery. After meeting his wife Yoko, he moved to Japan with his family in 2014. He began living in an old house that Yoko's grandmother used to live in, renovated a 90-year-old barn, and opened "Bäckerei Nagaya" in 2016. The store was entirely renovated by Mike himself.
He mills his own flour from local, low-chemical wheat and makes about 15 kinds of bread with organic ingredients and home-cultivated sourdough. The bakery attracts a steady stream of customers , including local elders and even those from out of town.
Mike lives with his five children, grows vegetables, raises animals, and is surrounded by nature.

Owner: Stefan Mike (born in Berlin and raised in Munich, Germany)
Bakery's name: Bäckerei Nagaya
Location: 1894 Mawarigami-cho, Miyoshi City, Hiroshima Prefecture

Types of natural yeast
1, Sourdough
2, Rye Sourdough

Filming and Editing： REIYA Watanabe

snippet.title: SHE FARMS AND BUILT IT ALL FOR THE LOVE OF BREAD! [hitohi] | Japanese Bakery
snippet.description:
The bread is baked in the wood burning stone oven. You can smell the beautiful aroma as the bread absorbs the energy of the fire.
People cannot live without fire and hitohi captures that energy in their bread every day.
Hoping to provide happiness if not just for this day (hitohi) today.

Today, I would like to introduce to you Ms. Hiroko Yokota, the owner of the bakery hitohi, located in Shintomicho, Koyugun, Miyazaki. 
Kneading flour then baking. It seems easy. But everyone says that when she does it, it becomes something completely different. 
Her bread will lure you in just with its aroma and when you take one bite, it will fill you with happiness. It is very difficult to elevate bread into something that deeply moves you. But she does it with ease. 

~Japanese Bakery Tour~
Each Japanese bakery has its own unique personality. I created this channel to share my passion and aspirations as a baker. There are many bakeries around us. Please enjoy each story.
Please support us by liking, commenting, and subscribing to the channel! !

snippet.title: White Strawberry Tart Recipe
snippet.description:
▼ Ingredients 18cm
・Dough
60ｇunsalted butter 
30ｇpowdered sugar
1 egg yolk
110ｇcake flour （not 100g）
・Custard Cream
250ｇmilk
３egg yolks
60ｇsuger
20ｇcorn starch
1tspVanilla extract
・Crème d'amandes (almond cream)
40ｇunsalted butter 
40ｇpowdered sugar
1 egg yolk
60ｇalmond flour
6ｇcorn starch(２tsp)

16p strawberrys
100ml heavy cream
8ｇsugar

▼ Directions
-Dough
① Mix soft butter and powdered sugar
② Add egg yolk to the bowl and mix well, sift flour and put together the dough
③ wrap the dough with plastic-wrap and chill it in the refrigerator
-Custard Cream
④ Add sugar to milk and put it on fire
⑤ Mix egg yolk, sugar and corn starch, add boiled milk in three parts, mix and return it to the pot
⑥ Make the fire medium heat and boil it steadily while mixing with a whisk
⑦ Add vanilla extract to the cream, transfer it to the bowl, put a plastic-wrap on it and let it cool well in the refrigerator
-Crème d'amandes (almond cream)
⑧ Add sugar to soft butter and stir it adding the beaten eggs little by little. Adding corn starch in the middle of this makes it easy to mix
⑨ Add almond flower and mix
-Baking
⑩ Lightly knead the tart dough and stretch it bigger than the mold with a rolling pin
⑪ Spread the dough in a mold, make some holes with a fork, put crème d'amandes (almond cream) and flatten it
⑫ Bake it in an oven at 180 ° C for 25 to 30 minutes
-Finishing
⑬ Mix the custard cream well with the electric whisk to make it smooth, and place it on the tart
⑭ Cut strawberries in half and arrange
⑮ Add sugar to fresh cream and whip it and squeeze it out around the tart with a squeezing bag.

localized.title: White Strawberry Tart Recipe
localized.description:
▼ Ingredients 18cm
・Dough
60ｇunsalted butter 
30ｇpowdered sugar
1 egg yolk
110ｇcake flour （not 100g）
・Custard Cream
250ｇmilk
３egg yolks
60ｇsuger
20ｇcorn starch
1tspVanilla extract
・Crème d'amandes (almond cream)
40ｇunsalted butter 
40ｇpowdered sugar
1 egg yolk
60ｇalmond flour
6ｇcorn starch(２tsp)

16p strawberrys
100ml heavy cream
8ｇsugar

▼ Directions
-Dough
① Mix soft butter and powdered sugar
② Add egg yolk to the bowl and mix well, sift flour and put together the dough
③ wrap the dough with plastic-wrap and chill it in the refrigerator
-Custard Cream
④ Add sugar to milk and put it on fire
⑤ Mix egg yolk, sugar and corn starch, add boiled milk in three parts, mix and return it to the pot
⑥ Make the fire medium heat and boil it steadily while mixing with a whisk
⑦ Add vanilla extract to the cream, transfer it to the bowl, put a plastic-wrap on it and let it cool well in the refrigerator
-Crème d'amandes (almond cream)
⑧ Add sugar to soft butter and stir it adding the beaten eggs little by little. Adding corn starch in the middle of this makes it easy to mix
⑨ Add almond flower and mix
-Baking
⑩ Lightly knead the tart dough and stretch it bigger than the mold with a rolling pin
⑪ Spread the dough in a mold, make some holes with a fork, put crème d'amandes (almond cream) and flatten it
⑫ Bake it in an oven at 180 ° C for 25 to 30 minutes
-Finishing
⑬ Mix the custard cream well with the electric whisk to make it smooth, and place it on the tart
⑭ Cut strawberries in half and arrange
⑮ Add sugar to fresh cream and whip it and squeeze it out around the tart with a squeezing bag.

Thank you for your cooperation in translation.

snippet.title: Sub) Giant Strawberry Rose Macarons
snippet.description:
We post unpublished photos and videos on YouTube to the Instagram. 
➢ https://www.instagram.com/emojoiecuisine

➢Ingredients 15cm macaron
65g egg white
70g granulated sugar
Food coloring
70g almond flour
70g powdered sugar
150℃ 13 min. small macaroons
           24 min. large macaroons

➢Crème à la rose
2 egg whites
100g granulated sugar
230g unsalted butter
Rose aroma and essence
*Need to adjust the amount.
2 egg yolks
40g granulated sugar
100g milk

➢Fruits
18 strawberries
Raspberries, pomegranates, etc.

1)  3:22
・Macaron
Warm up the egg white and granulated sugar at 50 ° C and add the food colouring to make a meringue.

2) 4:31
Add the grind almonds from 1) and powdered sugar, then mix it with a rubber spatula.
Mix until just before the traces of dropping the dough disappear slowly.

3) 5:31
Fill a pastry bag with 2) and squeeze the dough into a 15 cm circle. Make small macaroons with the remaining dough.

4) 6:54
Piled up two oven plates. Bake at 150 ° C for small macaroons for 13 minutes and 150 ° C for large macaroons for 24 minutes.

5) 8:24
・Rose cream
Warm up the egg white and granulated sugar to 50 ° C to make a meringue.
Microwave the unsalted butter to about 25 ° C and add the aroma of the rose. 
I added 1 tablespoon of aroma in the video, but adjust the amount depending on the manufacturer and type.

6) 9:35
Add slightly warm milk to a mixture of egg yolk and granulated sugar and return to the pot.
Heat to 80 ° C while mixing the bottom of the pot well, and whisk with an electric whipper.

7) 11:30
Add 6) to unsalted butter little by little, mix well, and add the meringue.
* Please note that butter and 6) will separate if it’s cold.

8) 12:46
Assemble with macaron, cream and strawberries.
Macaroons become moist when put in the refrigerator for about half a day to keep them from drying. Harden the remaining cream in a container with strawberries. If you cool the cream down in the refrigerator and then reheat it, the bubbles will disappear and the cream will not melt in your mouth.

-----------------------------------------------------------------
* Preheating is necessary. Even if the recipe was written without "preheat oven ...", you must preheat the oven, and please start baking when the oven reaches a set temperature.

* The result of baking may be changed depending on each oven at home. The temperature and the baking time in this recipe is only a guide. 
Please check the degree of baking stuff before taking it out from the oven, and then take it out.

#Ispahan #macaron

snippet.title: Mille Crepe Recipe with French Crepes
snippet.description:
ーTurn on the subtitlesー
You can turn on the subtitles for the recipe.
Change the language from the top right of the screen for the mobile phone.
For the PC, from the bottom right of the screen.

▼Ingredients 
➢20 crepes 17cm
200g all-purpose flour
*Or 100g bread flour and 100g cake flour
100g sugar
A pinch of salt（0.5g)
2 eggs
400g milk 
50g dark rum
50g melted butter（unsalt）*Not 25g
1 tbsp vanilla extract
➢Gianduja
75g hazelnuts
15g powdered sugar
25g olive oil
75g milk chocolate
➢Cream
200g whipping cream
200g mascarpone
*If the fat content of the fresh cream is 35% or more, you can make it without using mascarpone. In that case, the whipping cream is 35% 400g.

Moule en silicone pour bande Big Tourbillon 100
https://www.amazon.fr/dp/B01N2AZSR4

1)  Gianduja 0:55
Bake hazelnuts in an oven at 150 ° C for 30-40 minutes.
Paste nuts and powdered sugar with a food processor
Add olive oil and mix with melted milk chocolate.
Pour into a silicone mold and freeze.

2)Crepe dough 3:34
Add an egg and milk at room temperature to the flour and then mix it.
Add other ingredients when mixed it well.

3)How to bake crepes 6:14
Bake crepes in a frying pan heated to 180 - 200 ° C.
On low heat.
Make about 20 crepes of 17cm with 40g dough.

4)Cream 8:54
Add sugar to 30% fat cream and mascarpone and then whisk while it cooling the bowl with ice.
If the cream with a fat content of 35% or more can be made without mascarpone.

5)Put together 9:55
Use 16 crepes to apply cream and layer
Put some cream with 16 crepes while making a layer on top of another.
Put some gianduja on and then put the frozen gianduja on it.

-----------------------------------------------------------------

▼SUBSCRIBE

snippet.title: MEGA COMPILATION OF 5-MINUTE CRAFTS
snippet.description:
BEST CRAFTS EVER

Today we share a mega compilation of awesome crafts to spend evenings with fun! You will find crafts with stationary, paper crafts, cool crafts from concrete, toys ideas and a lot more! 
Let’s start from drawing ideas you will totally love! We share drawing exercises to boost your imagination! Follow our tutorial and try to make quick and easy pictures with cats, town and even aliens! 
You can make cool storage boxes and even a small dresser out of carboard boxes. There is always not enough boxes and containers to keep your home organized. That’s why we share helpful ideas how to up-cycle cardboard boxes into beautiful instant storage boxes! 
You will find some lovely paper crafts that are so easy to make! Get your color paper, tissues, and scissors and let's get creative! There are a lot of origami ideas to make and even you can make jumping frogs to play with your friends!
Ribbons look so elegant and you can create a lot of things using ribbons! Use ribbons of different colors and create a unique and fancy notebook cover. Watch the tutorial to learn how to put ribbons in the form of chess squares. Do you need a new headband or keychain? And again we are ready to help! 
Concrete is a perfect material to create cute decoration items for your home! You will learn how to make concrete planters, candle holders, letters and even the furniture! Make cook concrete planters to upgrade your interior design. Moreover, you can paint your planters any color that suits your house!
If you adore plants and want to make something special or even a create fairy tail at home, you will love our ideas how to decorate mini gardens. You will find how to make different items by your own hands. You can even create a sense of childlike magic creating a small house for Tinker Bell or any character you like. Have fun!
Every girl loves dolls and especially Barbie! Find a ton of ideas how to make accessory, furniture and clothes for Barbie from ordinary things you already have at home! You can create a whole new world for your Queen without spending a ton of money! Be creative and have fun!

snippet.title: Easy Ways To Upgrade Your Bedroom || Cool Home Organizing And Decorating Hacks
snippet.description:
Does your bedroom lack creativity and color? Stop thinking that your bedroom is boring anymore. Today we are going to give you many renovation and decoration ideas so that you can upgrade your personal space. Get ready for a whole new look, and you can even use recyclable or everyday items to easily renovate any space. Are you ready to make your own DIY decoration crafts? Don’t waste more time!

If you want to learn fun and easy ways to redecorate any room in your home, stay and watch this video. Here you will learn how to use plastic tubes to create a new headboard in your own style or to add a lot of volume to your curtains. We show you how to transform tires into a unique coffee table. Build your own benches and comfortable armchairs. Use acrylic paint to repair a broken plate and turn it into an art piece. You can even create all kinds of organizers to use in your kitchen, your bathroom or your closet. Everything is easier than you imagine!

TIMESTAMPS:
20:36 - Hanging bed organizar

30:02 - Service table with clothes hangers

01:19:41 - Rim sofa

01:49:48 - DIY Garbage bag dispenser

02:11:54 - Jewelry box with cork

snippet.title: Ep : 5 I Jain Philosophy: An Introduction I Dr Vikas Divyakirti
snippet.description:
To follow on Instagram, visit: https://www.instagram.com/divyakirti.vikas/

 
प्रिय साथियो,
 
दर्शन सीरीज़ में एक बार फिर से आपका स्वागत है!
 
दर्शन सीरीज़ के इस पाँचवें एपिसोड में 'जैन दर्शन (Jain Philosophy)' विषय पर चर्चा की गई है। इसमें मेरी कोशिश है कि जैन दर्शन से जुड़े कुछ बुनियादी प्रश्नों जैसे- जैन दर्शन क्या है? इसके सिद्धांत क्या हैं? जैन धर्म और हिंदू धर्म में क्या अंतर है? जैन समुदाय ईश्वर को नहीं मानता तो वर्धमान महावीर को भगवान महावीर क्यों कहते हैं? जैन समुदाय के लोग संख्या में इतने कम हैं, फिर भी वे इतने समृद्ध कैसे हुए? स्यादवाद का संबंध आर्टिफिशियल इंटेलिजेंस से बनता है, क्या यह सच है? और आत्मा के अस्तित्व और जगत के निर्माण व संचालन को लेकर इनका विचार कैसे शेष दर्शनों से अलग है एवं वर्तमान समाज में इनकी प्रासंगिकता किस रूप में है? इन सभी पक्षों से गुज़रना संभवतः आपके लिये रुचिकर रहे!

इस सेशन के लिये हमने पहली बार लगभग 100 दर्शकों को आमंत्रित किया था। ये दर्शक उन 3000+ आवेदकों में से थे जिन्होंने ऑनलाइन फ़ॉर्म भरकर ऐसी इच्छा व्यक्त की थी। आगामी सत्रों में भी यह परंपरा जारी रहेगी। यदि आपने फॉर्म भरा था तो जल्दी ही आपके पास भी बुलावा आएगा; और यदि नहीं भरा था किंतु भरना चाहते हैं तो कृपया इस लिंक पर जाकर फॉर्म भर सकते हैं : https://vikasdivyakirti.com/register
 
शुभकामनाओं सहित, 
विकास दिव्यकीर्ति

इस वीडियो में आपकी सुविधा के लिए टाइम स्टैम्प दिया गया है, जिसके माध्यम से आप सीधे संबंधित टॉपिक्स को देख सकते हैं:

00:00 पृष्ठभूमि (Introduction)
2:47 दर्शन सीरीज़ का उद्देश्य
5:20 जैन दर्शन को कैसे समझें?
15:23 जैन दर्शन का वर्गीकरण
19:14 तत्‍वमीमांसा (Metaphysics) क्या है?
30:34 अनेकांतवाद
40:54 दुनिया में क्या-क्या अस्तित्व में है?
44:14 आत्मा क्या है?
01:05:26 आत्मा के प्रकार
01:10:36  संसार/जगत कैसे बना?
01:16:11 ईश्वर/तीर्थंकर 
01:23:45 जैन ज्ञानमीमांसा
01:27:05 ज्ञान के प्रकार
01:41:43 स्यादवाद
01:51:35 संदेहवाद
01:57:39 अज्ञेयवाद
02:09:36 सप्तभंगीनय
02:16:57 स्यादवाद का महत्त्व
02:20:13 स्यादवाद और आर्टिफिशियल इंटेलिजेंस का संबंध
02:25:45 जैन नीतिमीमांसा
02:27:23 बंधन क्या है?
02:31:46 मोक्ष/कैवल्य
02:40:00 जैन दर्शन की प्रासंगिकता

इस सेशन के लिये हमने पहली बार लगभग 100 दर्शकों को आमंत्रित किया था। ये दर्शक उन 3000+ आवेदकों में से थे जिन्होंने ऑनलाइन फ़ॉर्म भरकर ऐसी इच्छा व्यक्त की थी। आगामी सत्रों में भी यह परंपरा जारी रहेगी। यदि आपने फॉर्म भरा था तो जल्दी ही आपके पास भी बुलावा आएगा; और यदि नहीं भरा था किंतु भरना चाहते हैं तो कृपया इस लिंक पर जाकर फॉर्म भर सकते हैं : https://vikasdivyakirti.com/register

snippet.description:

दर्शन सीरीज़ के इस तीसरे एपिसोड में 'अंतिम सत्य क्या है'  विषय पर चर्चा की गई है। इसमें मेरी कोशिश है कि आप दर्शन से जुड़े कुछ बुनियादी प्रश्नों जैसे- अंतिम सत्य क्या है, यह सवाल कहॉं से आया, इस संबंध में अब तक क्या उत्तर खोजे गए हैं और अभी उन सब की क्या प्रासंगिकता है आदि को ठीक से समझ सकें। इसके साथ ही यह दुनिया कैसे बनी और किसने बनाई जैसी जिज्ञासाओं को भी तार्किक ढंग से समझने-समझाने का प्रयत्न किया गया है। 

अगर आपके मन में भी ऐसे प्रश्न उठते हैं और आप इनका तार्किक उत्तर जानने की इच्छा रखते हैं तो यह चर्चा निश्चित ही आपके लिये सहायक होगी।

snippet.title: Ep : 2 | Introduction of Indian Philosophy from Vedas to Osho by Dr. Vikas Divyakirti
snippet.description:
इंस्टाग्राम पर जुड़ना चाहें, तो यह रहा पता : https://instagram.com/divyakirti.vikas?igshid=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==



भारतीय दर्शन की लंबी और समृद्ध परंपरा रही है। वैदिक काल से लेकर बौद्ध-जैन और फिर आधुनिक काल तक भारतीय दर्शन का वैविध्यपूर्ण स्वरूप निर्मित हुआ है। इसलिये इसकी गहराइयों में जाने के पूर्व यह आवश्यक ही है कि हम इसकी मूलभूत विशेषताओं से परिचित हो जाएँ और इसके विकासक्रम को ठीक से समझ लें। 

इस वीडियो में मैंने कोशिश की है कि आप संक्षेप में भारतीय दर्शन की बुनियादी विशेषताओं, इसकी विकास यात्रा, प्रमुख दार्शनिक और उनके विचार आदि से अवगत हो जाएँ। मुझे उम्मीद है कि दर्शन और उसके सिद्धांतों को जानने-समझने की इच्छा रखने वाले साथियों के लिये यह चर्चा विषय प्रवेश की तरह सहायक हो सकेगी।

snippet.title: यूरोप में लोगों को और काम करना चाहिए? [Europe's labor landscape – Should Europeans work more?]
snippet.description:
यूरोप में पहले ही कर्मचारी बाकी दुनिया की तुलना में कम घंटे काम करते हैं. अब वे काम के घंटों को और कम किए जाने की मांग कर रहे हैं. यहां काम के घंटे कम क्यों हैं और क्या उन्हें और कम किया गया, तब भी पश्चिमी यूरोपीय अर्थव्यवस्थाओं का काम चल जाएगा? #dwbusiness #jobs #work 
The labor landscape has changed in some of Europe's wealthiest countries. More people are working – but for fewer hours on average. With a generation of workers now heading for the exits, governments and employers are trying to make working more more attractive. Can they succeed?

🙏గౌరవనీయులైన తల్లిదండ్రులారా..🙏

మీ పిల్లల విద్యా  సామర్ధ్యం ఎంతో మీకు తెలుసా?🤷‍♂️

విద్య సామర్ధ్యం పరీక్షించటానికి 
🖥️"ఆర్టిఫీషియల్ ఇంటెలిజెన్స్ స్ట్రీమ్ అండ్ కెరియర్ టెస్ట్"🖥️

👉ఇప్పుడు Online లో అందుబాటులో ఉంది.

మీ పిల్లల సామర్ధ్యం ఎంత? ఏయే అంశాలపై వారికి పట్టు ఉంది, వారి విషయ పరిజ్ఞానం ఏమిటి? అనేది తెలుసు కుంటే  వాళ్ళు ఏ రంగంలో రాణిస్తారు అని ఇట్టే అంచనా వేయవచ్చు.

👉ఈ లక్ష్యం తోనే విద్యా రంగంలో 20 సంవత్సారాలు అనుభవం ఉన్న  అధ్యాపక బృందంచే " Dr.TCS  కెరియర్ గైడెన్స్ అండ్ కౌన్సెలింగ్" కేంద్రం ఏర్పాటు చేయడం జరిగింది.

ఈ టెస్ట్ యొక్క ముఖ్య ఉద్దేశం : 

1) విద్యార్థులు తమ జీవితం లో సరైన భవిష్యత్తు మార్గాన్ని ఎంచుకోవడానికి 

2) విద్యార్థులు  తమని గురించి తాము పూర్తిగా తెలుసుకొనగలరు 

3) విద్యార్థులు అంతర్లీనంగా వున్నా తమ యొక్క శక్తి యుక్తులను ,నైపుణ్యాన్ని మరియు వ్యక్తిత్వాన్ని తెలుసుకొనగలరు మరియు వారి IQ ,EQ,CQ, and AQ  లెవెల్స్ తెలుసుకొనవచ్చును 

👉భవిష్యత్ అవసరాలకు తగిన నైపుణ్యాలు విద్యార్థులకు ఏ రంగంలో ఉన్నాయో తెలుసుకునేందుకు ఈ పరీక్ష ఉపయోగపడుతుంది. తదనుగుణంగా  విద్యావిధానంలో మార్పులు చేయడానికి ఇది దోహదం చేస్తుంది.

👉ప్రశ్నపత్రం ఆంగ్లంలో ఉంటుంది.

👉విద్యార్థులు వారి ఇంటి నుంచే ఆన్ లైన్ లో వారికీ వీలైన సమయములోనే పరీక్ష రాయవచ్చు .

👉పరీక్షలో భాగంగా పలురకాల నైపుణ్యాలను  పరీక్షి స్తారు.గణాంకాలు,అనలిటికల్ రీజనింగ్,వెర్బల్ ఎబిలిటీ తదితర 14 విభాగాల నుండి ప్రశ్నలుంటాయి.

👉13 నుండి 25 సంవత్సరాల విద్యార్థులు (8 వ తరగతి ఆ పైన ) పాల్గొనవచ్చు.

👉విద్యార్థులు  సాధించిన మార్కుల పై 55 పేజీల స్పష్టమైన  నివేక ( Career Guidance Report )  ఇవ్వడం జరుగుతుంది.

👉మరిన్ని వివరాలకు : 9032270597 

👉విద్యార్థులకు ఉచిత కౌన్సిలింగ్ ఇవ్వబడును   

👉ఆన్ లైన్ పరీక్షకు  రుసుము చెల్లించవలెను.

👉పరీక్ష సమయం : 60   నిమిషములు

🙏మీ పిల్లల భవిష్యత్తుకు ఉపయోగ పడే ఈ విలువైన సమాచారాన్ని దయచేసి మీ మిత్రులతో 
 షేర్ చెయ్యగలరు.🙏

మీ పిల్లల సామర్ధ్యం ఎంత? ఏయే అంశాలపై వారికి పట్టు ఉంది, వారి విషయ పరిజ్ఞానం ఏమిటి? అనేది తెలుసు కుంటే  వాళ్ళు ఏ రంగంలో రాణిస్తారు అని ఇట్టే అంచనా వేయవచ్చు.

👉ఈ లక్ష్యం తోనే విద్యా రంగంలో 20 సంవత్సారాలు అనుభవం ఉన్న  అధ్యాపక బృందంచే " Dr.TCS  కెరియర్ గైడెన్స్ అండ్ కౌన్సెలింగ్" కేంద్రం ఏర్పాటు చేయడం జరిగింది.

ఈ టెస్ట్ యొక్క ముఖ్య ఉద్దేశం : 

1) విద్యార్థులు తమ జీవితం లో సరైన భవిష్యత్తు మార్గాన్ని ఎంచుకోవడానికి 

2) విద్యార్థులు  తమని గురించి తాము పూర్తిగా తెలుసుకొనగలరు 

3) విద్యార్థులు అంతర్లీనంగా వున్నా తమ యొక్క శక్తి యుక్తులను ,నైపుణ్యాన్ని మరియు వ్యక్తిత్వాన్ని తెలుసుకొనగలరు మరియు వారి IQ ,EQ,CQ, and AQ  లెవెల్స్ తెలుసుకొనవచ్చును 

👉భవిష్యత్ అవసరాలకు తగిన నైపుణ్యాలు విద్యార్థులకు ఏ రంగంలో ఉన్నాయో తెలుసుకునేందుకు ఈ పరీక్ష ఉపయోగపడుతుంది. తదనుగుణంగా  విద్యావిధానంలో మార్పులు చేయడానికి ఇది దోహదం చేస్తుంది.

👉ప్రశ్నపత్రం ఆంగ్లంలో ఉంటుంది.

👉విద్యార్థులు వారి ఇంటి నుంచే ఆన్ లైన్ లో వారికీ వీలైన సమయములోనే పరీక్ష రాయవచ్చు .

👉పరీక్షలో భాగంగా పలురకాల నైపుణ్యాలను  పరీక్షి స్తారు.గణాంకాలు,అనలిటికల్ రీజనింగ్,వెర్బల్ ఎబిలిటీ తదితర 14 విభాగాల నుండి ప్రశ్నలుంటాయి.

👉13 నుండి 25 సంవత్సరాల విద్యార్థులు (8 వ తరగతి ఆ పైన ) పాల్గొనవచ్చు.

👉విద్యార్థులు  సాధించిన మార్కుల పై 55 పేజీల స్పష్టమైన  నివేక ( Career Guidance Report )  ఇవ్వడం జరుగుతుంది.

👉మరిన్ని వివరాలకు : 9032270597 

👉విద్యార్థులకు ఉచిత కౌన్సిలింగ్ ఇవ్వబడును   

👉ఆన్ లైన్ పరీక్షకు  రుసుము చెల్లించవలెను.

👉పరీక్ష సమయం : 60   నిమిషములు

🙏మీ పిల్లల భవిష్యత్తుకు ఉపయోగ పడే ఈ విలువైన సమాచారాన్ని దయచేసి మీ మిత్రులతో 
 షేర్ చెయ్యగలరు.🙏

Hey Everyone! ) I’m Anna and welcome to my channel. Here, I post some useful information for English learners. I’m from Ukraine and I’ve worked on my English and accent, for the most part, on my own, but you can find out and trace my story by watching my videos. I’ve been studying American pronunciation for a long time, and I still do, and I guess I always will – because it’s not math. Learning a language, it’s a lifetime journey. I know exactly what it takes to become fluent and acquire an accent in a non-English speaking country, and I’ve never even been to one. And I’m sharing this information here – on my channel. 

Speak English with me PLAYLIST:
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLIfikc3B11tp5wyOl11LomK8cIvJ8Ymzy

SHADOWING TECHNIQUE: Are you doing it right?
https://youtu.be/zWioMxOpOIk

Shadowing technique (mimicking) demonstration
https://youtu.be/DPkk0lfOrlc

Who should you choose to SHADOW? / My Example of Perfect Pronunciation
https://youtu.be/c9DjHuageIQ

snippet.title: Level Up Your English Vocabulary! Learn these 10 English common words synonyms!
snippet.description:
✅Download my English book (for FREE!): 
https://pocenglish.com/book/

✅Become a channel member:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC9CohF5QlJr3md4h9iTLzOg/join
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
👉 The reason why many students think their English is bad, is because they use simple vocabulary all the time! For example, if you want to describe something positively, you would use adjectives such as "Nice, Good", or negatively using adjectives such as "Bad". In this lesson, you will learn some alternatives to simple adjectives that you use daily. 

These words are as follows:
✔️  Good
✔️ Bad
✔️ Very
✔️ Interesting
✔️ Nice
✔️ Happy
✔️ Sad
✔️ Big
✔️ Small

👉 Improving your English vocabulary is the first step in improving your overall English level. Substituting simple words would make you sound more professional and advanced while trying to communicate in English.

👉In this video, you'll learn 15 common English idioms that you can use in your daily conversations! Idioms are phrases that don't mean what they seem to on the surface, but once you understand them, they can really help you communicate more fluently and naturally.

snippet.title: Formal English Phrases For Everyday Conversation!
snippet.description:
✅Download my English book (for FREE!): 
https://pocenglish.com/book/

✅Become a channel member:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC9CohF5QlJr3md4h9iTLzOg/join
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
👉 English can be formal, semi formal or informal. Depending on the situation, you can use one of these registers. There is no better or worse. If you are hanging out with friends, you use informal English. When talking to your professor or giving a lecture at university, you use Formal English. 

👉 Formal phrases in English are special words and sentences that we use when we want to be polite and respectful. They help us communicate in a nice and proper way, especially in more serious situations. For example, instead of saying "Hey!" you might say "Hello!" or "Hi there!" when you meet someone important or when you want to show good manners. Another formal phrase is "Please" when you ask for something, and "Thank you" when you want to show gratitude. Remember, using formal phrases is like using your best manners to show kindness and respect to others!

👉 In this lesson, you will learn some formal phrases for everyday English conversation! These can be used at work in any other formal setting.

👉 Where do you live? A house, or and apartment? Can you describe it? Tell me about your neighborhood!
In this lesson, we are going to learn all you need to describe the place where you live in English! That means we are going to see what English words, phrases and adjectives we can use to describe a house, an apartment, a neighborhood, a room, etc. 

👉 Some idioms and collocations mentioned in this video are as follows:
🔴 A detached house
🔴 A terraced house
🔴Spacious living room

snippet.description:

--------------------------------
In this video, you'll learn 30 common English idioms that native speakers use all the time. Idioms are phrases that don't mean what they seem to on the surface, but once you understand them, they can really help you communicate more fluently and naturally. 

You'll learn the meanings and usage of these 30 essential idioms, along with example sentences and tips for using them in conversation. By the end of the video, you'll be equipped with a powerful tool for sounding more like a native English speaker and communicating with greater confidence and ease.

To navigate easily, here are the timestamps:
➡️ Part 1
00:00 Intro
01:01 Beat around the bush
01:37 Bite off more than you can chew
02:28 A blessing in disguise
03:50 Give somebody the benefit of the doubt
04:37 Kill two birds with one stone
05:22 Let the cat out of the bag
05:57 Miss the boat
06:37 Take something with a grain of salt
07:50 Be up in the air
08:14 Stab somebody in the back
08:51 DIALOGUE 1

➡️Part 2
09:52 Lose your touch
10:38 Sit tight
11:08 Face the music
11:37 Get over somebody/ something
12:22 Crunch time 
13:03 Get out of hand
13:29 Get something out of your system
13:55 Hang in there
14:21 Throw caution to the wind
15:03 Call it a day
15:23 QUIZ TIME!

➡️Part 3
17:58 Be on cloud nine
18:23 Be under the weather
18:47 Speak of the devil
19:15 Ignorance is bliss
19:57 That ship has sailed
20:30 Bark up the wrong tree
21:12 On top of the world
21:35 Full of the joys of spring
22:06 Kick the bucket
22:37 Like death warmed up
22:55 DIALOGUE 2

I hope you enjoy this lesson!
Cheers
Maddy!

In this video, you'll learn common English idioms and words that you can use to talk about change! To give you a little exercise before watching this video, look at the following sentences:

👉I want to change my hairstyle

In the examples above, what word or idiom can you use instead of "Change"? Think about it! Then watch this lesson to learn!

snippet.description:

✅Become a channel member:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
👉English slang words are like secret words that some people use to talk in a cool and fun way. They're like special expressions that make talking more exciting. Just imagine if you had a super special way to say things that only your friends understood. That's what American slangs are for, to make talking extra awesome!

Instead of always saying the same old stuff, we use these fun words to add some flavor to our conversations. It's like having a secret code for words that everyone in the group understands. So, just like children have their own games and jokes, adults use slangs to have their own special way of talking and having a blast!

In this lesson, you will learn about the most common English slang words.

snippet.title: Formal and Informal words in English + examples (Part 4)
snippet.description:
✅Download my English book (for FREE!): 
https://pocenglish.com/book/

✅Become a channel member:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC9CohF5QlJr3md4h9iTLzOg/join
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
English can be formal, semi formal or informal. Depending on the situation, you can use one of these registers. There is no better or worse. If you are hanging out with friends, you use informal English. When talking to your professor or giving a lecture at university, you use Formal English. 

Imagine words are like clothes. Just like you wear different outfits for different occasions, we use different words for different situations. Formal words are like fancy clothes you wear to important events, like a wedding or a special party. They make you sound polite and respectful. Informal words are like your comfy everyday clothes that you wear when you're playing with friends or hanging out at home. They're more relaxed and casual. So, just like you choose the right outfit for each occasion, you choose the right words – formal or informal – to match the situation you're in!

In this lesson, you will learn some formal and informal words in English to improve your English vocabulary and knowledge! 

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

snippet.title: What are other words for but( synonyms for but) ? + example
snippet.description:
✅Download my English book (for FREE!): 
https://pocenglish.com/book/

✅Become a channel member:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC9CohF5QlJr3md4h9iTLzOg/join
-------------------------------------------------------------
When we talk about "but alternatives," we mean finding different options or choices instead of just sticking with one thing. It's like having more than one way to do things or more than one option to choose from. 

So, "but synonyms" is all about exploring different options and trying new things while still enjoying what you already like. It's like adding more color to your life and making it even more exciting! Just remember, it's okay to have favorites, but sometimes, discovering new alternatives can lead to wonderful surprises and adventures. 

👉In this English vocabulary lesson, you will learn some synonyms for but!  Is it wrong to say "but" all the time? No. Does it show you have a limited vocabulary? Yes! Therefore, learning different ways to say "but" will increase your vocabulary and help you sound more confident in the English language. In this English vocabulary.

snippet.title: Advanced English Vocabulary #shorts
snippet.description:
#shorts 

The reason why many students think their English is bad, is because they use simple vocabulary all the time! For example, if you want to describe something positively, you would use adjectives such as "Nice, Good", or negatively using adjectives such as "Bad". In this lesson, you will learn some alternatives to simple adjectives and simple verbs that you use daily. 

Improving your English vocabulary is the first step in improving your overall English level. Substituting simple words would make you sound more professional and advanced while trying to communicate in English.

snippet.title: Idioms with colors in English | A complete list of color idioms + example
snippet.description:
✅Become a channel member:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC9CohF5QlJr3md4h9iTLzOg/join

✅Download my English book (for FREE!): 
https://pocenglish.com/book/
--------------------------------
👉Idioms are words that are a group of words that have a meaning different than the direct meaning of the words themselves. For example, if something is a piece of cake, it doesn’t mean that it’s actually like a cake! It means that it’s very easy to do.

👉What we know about the use of colors in English is that they are mainly used as adjectives for describing the appearance of things or people. But there are some English idioms and English expressions with colors which are mainly used by native English speakers.

👉Using idioms with colors in English can be a lot of fun! It's like having a secret code to express our feelings in a special way. Imagine someone says they're "tickled pink." It doesn't mean they turned pink like a crayon, but that they're really happy and excited. Or if they say "I'm feeling on top of the world," it doesn't mean they're standing on a globe, but that they're feeling incredibly happy. These colorful expressions help us paint pictures with our words!

In this video you will learn the most common English idioms with colors. Here is the list:

🔴 Out of the blue
🔴Once in a blue moon
🔴 With flying colors
🔴Tickled pink
🔴In red
🔴Caught red-handed
🔴Black market
🔴Red tape
🔴White color workers

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🌐Follow the link below to read the article about idioms with colors in English:
https://pocenglish.com/idioms-with-colors-in-english/

snippet.title: English Grammar: Don't Make These Grammatical Mistakes!
snippet.description:
Join My Online English Courses Today & start learning English! to find out more, click here:
https://pocenglish.com/college/general-english/
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Want to receive free lesson summary PDF files? Click here: https://pocenglish.com/landing

English grammar rules are a real pain in the neck! For example, for how long have you been learning present tense, past tense and future tense? But you are still making mistakes, right? (not everyone, though). One of the best ways to learn English grammar rules and tenses is by learning from common grammatical mistakes. In this lesson you will learn 5 very common mistakes and how to avoid them! 

For many students, learning English grammar, learning different grammar rules and grammar tenses as well as different types of sentences is very boring. English grammar is often difficult to deal with. But, if you want to learn English , grammar is inevitable! Why is that? 

The English language has 6 main aspects to learn: 2 systems and 4 skills
Systems are: English grammar and English vocabulary
Skills are: Speaking, Reading, Writing and Listening
To fully learn the English language from 0 to 100, you have to focus on all these 6 aspects, and of course, the systems are the base for the rest! learning English grammar is very crucial if you want to speak fluently and improve your English listening, reading and writing skills. 

Below are other lessons about common English Grammar mistakes that I posted before. Make sure you watch them and avoid these mistakes! 

*5 Common English grammar mistakes for lower intermediate level*
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rCcEcpG8SYo&list=PL6u0nu0mz1fzSxDMvVPQPpnOp_zO6-Von&index=1&ab_channel=POCEnglish

*5 common grammar mistakes with tenses in English language and how to avoid them!*
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UPVVNpQda6A&list=PL6u0nu0mz1fzSxDMvVPQPpnOp_zO6-Von&index=3&ab_channel=POCEnglish

As always, let me know what you think! Cheers!

snippet.title: ONE HOUR ENGLISH LESSON TO UNDERSTAND FAST ENGLISH CONVERSATIONS (ADVANCED LISTENING LESSON)
snippet.description:

snippet.title: How To Speak English Fast And Understand Native Speakers
snippet.description:
Do natives speakers speak English very fast? Do we have to speak English fast? How can we understand native speakers? 
These are very common questions that student's often ask. We learn English language, but when we watch movies or listen to music, we don't understand anything! 

Well, there are many reasons why it can be difficult to understand native speakers. Maybe it is because they speak fast, maybe they link words in a sentence, or maybe your ears are not used to hearing their accents. However, there are things you can learn not only to understand native speakers, but you can also sound like them when you speak English! Watch this lesson to find out how to speak English fast and understand natives!

snippet.title: Forget Words When Speaking English? Here Is Why!
snippet.description:
"I know many English words, but when I speak English, I forget all of them". 
If this is your problem too, this video is for you! In this video you will learn a 100% proven method to use when learning new English vocabulary as well as improving your speaking and fluency. 

English language is full of words. But do we need to know all of them to speak English? of course not! In fact, you can speak English by knowing 1000 words only (although an advanced level requires at least 10-15k words). However, the problem is sometimes you know these English words, but when you want to speak English, you are lost for words. Why is that?

This video will reveal the secret for you. It is not about the quantity of English vocabulary you learn, but quality of the English words and method of learning new English vocabulary. I have explained a method that has worked for all my student's who had the same problem. Don't miss it!

As always, don't forget to let me know what you think about this method!

This video will reveal the secret for you. It is not about the quantity of English vocabulary you learn, but quality of the English words and method of learning new English vocabulary. I have explained a method that has worked for all my student's who had the same problem. Don't miss it!

As always, don't forget to let me know what you think about this method!

snippet.title: 10 Tools To Practice Your English (For Free!)
snippet.description:
Join My Online English Courses Today & start learning English! to find out more, click here:
https://pocenglish.com/college/general-english/

Want to receive free lesson summary PDF files? Click here: https://pocenglish.com/landing
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Want to practice your English without having to pay a penny? Watch this video to see the best 10 tools I have discovered and worked with during my 10-year experience as an English teacher:

1- Online dictionaries: Seems basic, but knowing how to work with a dictionary and what dictionary to use is crucial for every language learner. I always use Cambridge online dictionary: https://dictionary.cambridge.org/

2- Find collocations: Words are never alone in the English language, and the group of words that often go together are called collocations. My favorite tool to find Ennglish collocations is called OZDIC collocation dictionary: https://ozdic.com/

3- Pronunciation practice: You can check the pronunciation of words via an online dictionary, but how can you make sure your pronunciation is correct? Don't pay for mobile applications to correct your pronunciation! You can use Google! Watch the video to find out how to do that.

4- British podcast: To improve your listening skill, you can listen to podcasts. If you are a fan of British accent, use BBC 6-minute English podcast: https://www.bbc.co.uk/learningenglish/english/features/6-minute-english

5- American podcast: If you like the American accent, I recommend VOA podcasts to improve your listening skill: https://learningenglish.voanews.com/podcasts

6- Grammar checker: There are many tools you can use to check your grammar. One of the most reliable grammar checkers online is Quillbot. It is a very reliable tool to check your English grammar: https://quillbot.com/grammar-check

7- Paraphrasing: A very important skill you need in english writing is paraphrasing. A very good paraphrasing too is Quillbot. You can use this tool to paraphrase paragraphs in a fairly accurate way (and then use grammar checker to make sure the grammmar is correct): https://quillbot.com/

8- Speaking topics: To practice speaking, you may need topics and some leading questions to help you have a conversation. ESL discussions provides a vast directory of topics and cue cards: https://esldiscussions.com/

9- Finding movie bits: If you are a movie lover and want to practice the new idioms and phrases you have learned with pieces of movies, you can use this tool: https://yarn.co/

10- Games: A very fun method to practice your English is to play games! This website offers interactive games designed to improve your English: https://www.gamestolearnenglish.com/

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Want to receive free lesson summary PDF files? Click here: https://pocenglish.com/landing













Don't forget to give a thumbs-up! Cheers!

snippet.title: Speak English With Confidence (Job & University interview)
snippet.description:
Want to download my English book for FREE? Click here:
https://pocenglish.com/book/
-----------------------------------------------
Do you want to take the IELTS Exam and are worried about the speaking session? Or perhaps you are applying for a job and preparing for the interview? Maybe a university admission interview is upcoming? 

In order to ace an interview, you MUST speak English fluently, accurately and with confidence! But how? In this lesson, I will give you some valuable tips on how to speak English with confidence during an interview.

00:00 Intro
00:26 Download my English book
01:12 Make a good first impression
02:58 Handshake: yes or no?
03:56 Online interview
04:41 Know what to expect during an interview
07:32 Body language matters
09:15 As for repetition/ clarification
10:46 Never interrupt the interviewer/ examiner 
11:18 How to prepare for an interview in short time?

I hope you've enjoyed this lesson, and don't forget to leave a comment!
Cheers!
Maddy
